<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id74a1459d-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s152903"><num value="152903">§ 152903.</num><heading> Purposes</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The purposes of the corporation are as provided in the articles of incorporation and include a continuing commitment, on a national basis—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id74a1459e-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s152903/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> to conduct, record, and publish the results of research on the history and deeds of the American colonists;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id74a1459f-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s152903/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> to publish the memoirs of American colonists;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id74a145a0-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s152903/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content> to erect memorials to commemorate the history and deeds of the American colonists;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id74a145a1-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s152903/4"><num value="4">(4)</num><content> to promote respect and admiration for the institutions, laws, and flag of the United States;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id74a145a2-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s152903/5"><num value="5">(5)</num><content> to engage in mutual improvement and educational activities;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id74a145a3-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s152903/6"><num value="6">(6)</num><content> to establish scholarships to assist needy and deserving students and to promote the improvement of educational institutions;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id74a145a4-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s152903/7"><num value="7">(7)</num><content> to engage in volunteer service and make contributions to veterans hospitals; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id74a145a5-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s152903/8"><num value="8">(8)</num><content> to perform other charitable activities, including the national presidents’ projects, as may be provided in the articles of incorporation or bylaws of the corporation.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id74a145a6-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7">(<ref href="/us/pl/105/225">Pub. L. 105–225</ref>, <date date="1998-08-12">Aug. 12, 1998</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/112/1420">112 Stat. 1420</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/105/354/s1/10">Pub. L. 105–354, § 1(10)</ref>, <date date="1998-11-03">Nov. 3, 1998</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/112/3244">112 Stat. 3244</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
